character development via loot rewards strong social ties.<br>
<br>
character development via exp grinding does NOT reward strong social ties.<br>
<br>
If your going to take steps to deemphasis the importance of gear on mains then your also taking away one of the key rewards for being socially commited.   <br>
<br>
AA skills are the antithesis of development via gear.  they are horrid cause they create power in characters independant of their ability to exist and organize social structures.  they are to be blunt boring flat and one dimensional no matter how BRANCHY you make them.  its still gain of power via grind.<br>
<br>
whats the fuss about rewarding social ties in eq?  SOCIAL STRUCTURE IS THE ENDGAME.  its all of it... its the progression of the masses you make ties with.  its the thing that is complicated.  the thing that takes skill.  the thing that creates intrigue.  undermine that in eq2 and you undermine the long term health of eq2.<br>
